=== Etymology ===
Old English [[scieran]], from Germanic ''*skeran'', from Indo-European ''*(s)ker-''.  Cognate with Dutch [[scheren#Dutch|scheren]], German [[scheren#German|scheren]], Swedish [[skära]]; and (''from Indo-European'') with Greek [[κείρειν]] ‘cut off’, Latin [[caro]] ‘flesh’, Lithuanian [[skìrti]] ‘separate’, Welsh [[ysgar]] ‘separate’.

